    "body": "@obale  @karalabe - After some experimenting, I found the following:\r\n\r\n* After setting `\"eip158Block\": 0` in `genesis.json` and re-creating the chain, I can submit transactions and invoke `set()` on a simple storage contract successfully; no longer see the error and stalling chain.\r\n* However, `get()` continued to fail with `Error: Couldn't decode uint256 from ABI: 0x` error from web3/solidity. To resolve this I had to change `\"homesteadBlock\": 0` in `genesis.json`. Ref: @karalabe 's recommendation in #3653\r\n\r\nBoth of the above require re-create of the chain? Is there no other way out?",
